:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; orphans:0; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Restricting the amount of time citizens can speak at publ</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ic meetings. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; orphans:0; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Omission or inaccurate reporting of business conducted in public in minutes of meetings.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; orphans:0; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Making it difficult for citizens</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to obtain information, even when requested under the Freedom of Information Act.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; orphans:0; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Poor understanding of the eight prin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ciples of the Data Protection Act 1998 in dealing with citizens’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> personal data which </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">can lead</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to infringement of their rights. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; orphans:0; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Failure to provide opportunities for citizens from all cultures and backgrounds to influence local services. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">What safeguards</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> should be in place to deal with service providers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">who fail to deliver services, or who deliver services of an insufficient</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">quality?</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">They should be served with improvement notices. If they fail to improve, sanctions should </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">be applied,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> including contract </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">termination</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> if necessary. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">How do we ensure that best practice is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> shared so it can be replicated </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">in the context of greater diversity of provision?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">D</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">efine and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">agree what “best practice”</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> means</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, then gather case studies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">which demonstrate best practice which</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> can be used as a resource for citizens, local public</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">service commissioners and providers. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">What progress has been made in setting up </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">mutuals</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> as an effective</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">way of delivering public services?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">It is assumed that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">they will act in the best interests of the public. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There is a risk that they will not. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">In my locality a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">Local</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal"> Community Interest Company </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">provides NHS community </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">services which were </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">previously provided by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">a Primary Care Trust.  It is not subject to the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">Freedom of Information Act</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal"> (FOIA)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">. It does not provide any information to show whether the standards of care it provides meet any nationally accepted standards of best practice. Its Board meets monthly. However the board meetings are not publicly advertise</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">d, therefore they are presumably closed to citizens to attend, even as observers. Meeting minutes are not made public. Consequently it is difficult</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal"> if not impossibl</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">e,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal"> for citizens to find out whether this </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">organisation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal"> is effective at delivering public ser</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">vices. </span></h1><h1 style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">Earlier this year the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal"> Community Interest Company made the local news when it was reported that its chair and four non-executive directors had resigned over a dispute about executive board members’ pay.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">This issue concerned the spending of public money, yet citizens were disempowered from scrutinizing the issue and the quality of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">organisations’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal"> leadership because it conducts its business in secret. </span></h1><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Summary </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The principle of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">giving</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">more power to cit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">izens good, but I am not convinced that the majority of citizens want it and have the time to devote to it. M</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">y experience is that the culture and leadership of some organisations which have responsibility for public services is nowhere near sufficiently de</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">veloped to provide genuine transparency, openness and public accoun</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">tability. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">O</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rganisations such as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">mutuals</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">which are not subject to the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">FOIA</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">taking over responsibility for services which were prev</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">iously managed by public bodies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> which were subject to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the FOIA.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This is an obstacle to greater openness, transparency and public accountability. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">If services are decentralised at a faster rate than local providers develop strong leadership and commitment to public service values and accountability, the conse</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">quence for citizens will be that they wi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">l</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">l be disempowered and silenced.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> November </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">2013 </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 18pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><img src="data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAgAAAATCAYAAACtHkzTAAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1BAACxjwv8YQUAAAAJcEhZcwAADsMAAA7DAcdvqGQAAAAiSURBVChTY2AYouA/LneDJGAYr99wmgDTNQIUEB1YVEwlAPhPDvJF3EtBAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC" width="8" height="18" alt="" style="float:left; margin:0pt" /></p></div></body></html>